ected Agentic because behavior text is explicitly pre-dispatch budget enforcement, not classification quality.","test_description":"Wire classifier to stub dispatcher and real token-counting component used in production. Send an over-budget document and assert policy outcome (truncate or reject) occurs and dispatcher is called only when post-policy request is within budget.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported token usage for a typical document stays within the configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Catching real failures requires real provider responses (including provider-side token accounting) on a real AI API path; stubs can mask mismatches between local expectations and provider-reported usage. Although assertion is deterministic, execution depends on real model API behavior/metadata. Rejected System-only framing because this is specifically tied to real AI API call semantics, not generic HTTP behavior.","test_description":"Execute live classification calls on representative documents and assert provider-reported token usage metadata is <= configured budget; fail if any call exceeds budget, and log model/version for reproducibility.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.29,"Agentic":0.63,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is retry-orchestration behavior across classifier, backoff policy, and API client; it can be reproduced with in-process stubbed 429 responses and controllable clock. Integration-brake check: no real OS/network/subprocess required, no dependence on model output content, and no m